name: Und das Leben wird voller Gift sein
Paura di vivere - Delitti d'amore - Il mistero dell'Isola d'Yd

description: Storm heads to Marrow to go find his friends Ember and Nomad. But against his will he gets roped into the Barsaman tournament. Storm escapes but is immediatly a wanted man with a wanderkiller in pursuit sent by Marduk. Storm leaves clues behind for Storm and Nomad so they can find him but the wanderkiller can decrypt the clues as well...
name: Het Rode Spoor

description: On their way to Anker, Storm, Ember and Nomad rescue a pilot after he crashses his airship. They take him to Anker where he's wanted for mutiny. The mutineer escapes though and takes Ember hostage with him. Storm pursues Ember while Nomad prepares the people of Anker for an all-out battle with the mutineers.
name: De Muiters van Anker

description: The Switchguards take good care of the Gulfstream but it turns out it can also be used as a formidable weapon. Unknown warriors plan to attack Nomads home kingdom using the Gulfstream. Storm, Ember and Nomad naturally give it their all to thwart this plan but is it enough to best these criminals who turn out to be from their past?
name: De Wisselwachters

description: Storm ends up in Sandrikan, the main place for gambling in Pandarve. Due to circumstances he's forced to enter the Opal Race, a deadly race run by gambling syndicates. And they have no intention of letting Storm finish that race alive...
name: De Race van Opaal

description: Storm, Ember and Nomad, once again, come eye to eye with Marduk, the Theocrate of Pandarve. But this time the roles are reversed. Fearing for his life, the theocrate flees into the coral garden of the Barkol castle. A strange and dangerous place populated by even weirder creatures. Storm, however, is determined to take care of his old nemesis once and for all.
name: Het Koraal van Kesmee

description: The Roman Centurion Caius Bonus wants to discover how it is possible that this one small village manages to resist the might of the Roman Empire. He sends a spy into the village who finds out that the Gauls have a magic potion that gives them super human strength. This potion can be made by one person only, the village druid, Panoramix. When he learns about this, Caius Bonus plans to capture the druid, force to make the potion for him so he can dethrone Julius Caesar. Naturally Asterix doesn't accept the fact that their druid has been kidnapped and sets out to get him back.
name: Asterix de Galliër

description: It's a small disaster for the Gaul village when the druid breaks his one golden sickle. Without it he won't be able to brew the magical potion that makes the village invincible. Asterix and Obelix are sent to Lutetia (Paris) to buy a new one but for some reason they need to fight themselves through a golden sickle cartel first...
name: Het Gouden Snoeimes

description: Asterix and Obelix accompany their druid Panoramix to a druids competition in Mistletoe Forest since they find it to dangerous for him to travel alone. Since they aren't allowed not being druids into the forest they wait by the forest edge for him. Meanwhile a group of Goths has invaded Gaul to find a druid that can help them overthrow Julius Caesar. Panoramix wins the competition with his magical strength potion and the Goths kidnap him. Asterix and Obelix feel they have to wait to long for their druid so they go and search for him deep into Goth territory.
name: Asterix en de Gothen

The great battle enters its third day as tensions rise in the Pandava Camp when brother turns against brother. Arrogant Bhima decides to take on the entire Kaurava army on his own while Arjuna's son Abhimanyu questions his role in this war. Meanwhile Duryodhana has a plan to stop Bhima in his tracks with the help of one of his secret weapons.

description: In this second Absolute edition, outlaw journalist Spider Jerusalem learns of the vicious murder of political consultant Vita Severn, one of the few people he liked, which leads him to delve into the city's police corruption. Then, Spider is hot on the trail of the horrifying truth behind the newly elected president's campaign. Collects issues #19-36.
name: Volume 2

description: By Odin's beard! The secret book of Thor's perverted sex life has fallen into the hands of a mere mortal! Obviously, Loki (disguised as a clown) is more than happy to take the book and use it for his own gain to humiliate the god of thunder but can Thor (disguised as a monkey) manage to get to the book first?

volume.name: Alterna Anniverseries: The Big Bad Book

description: Spidey and Silk's time jaunt takes them all the way to their beginning...the science fair where they were bitten by the radioactive spider! Plus: Chronosaurus Rex revealed!
name: Chapter Six

volume.name: Amazing Spider-Man & Silk: Spider(Fly) Effect Infinite Comic

description: After a fierce explosion rocks The Hidden's base camp, Arthur King, a.k.a. Malcolm Merlyn, discovers a traitor in their midst!
name: Part Two: The Rise of Arthur King Chapter 7: Traitor

description:
In early 1945 the skies above Dresden burned brightly with the fire of an almighty Allied bombing raid that would go down in history.

Unfortunately for "Jelly" Jakes of the Convict Commandos, he happened to be on a secret mission in the heart of the German city that fateful night when all hell broke loose.

If he managed to survive the relentless bombardment he would also have to contend with a blast from the Commandos' past.
name: Web of Fire

description:
The letter read:

"I, Count Ernst Von Steiger, the Red Arrow, challenge the leader of this squadron to a personal duel at noon tomorrow. I shall be waiting at 16,000 feet at British Map Ref. 481609."

And just before noon a lone Spitfire took off. At the controls was young Mike Carson, the pilot they called 'King of the Spits'!

During World War I, Lieutenant Trevor Waite was an infantry officer posted to the colony of British East Africa. Somehow he found himself serving as part of a boat squadron. Although no sailor, he was compelled to do his duty and prove his worth to the obnoxious C.O. who was convinced that Trevor was a coward.

Although Trevor's vessels were sturdy, reliable dhows, it looked like they might have met their match in the Germans' superior Type 1885 torpedo boats...
name: Action Africa!

description:
The traffic and the marching men were all heading in one direction... away from the advancing Germans and towards the port of Dunkirk. Only there did the retreating British troops have a chance of being evacuated to England.

However, one truck was heading the other way and it was not by mistake. Two British soldiers and a middle‑aged bank manager were staging their own FIGHTING RETURN!
name: Fighting Return

description: Frank Castle's hunt has taken him on the road, and bodies will be left in his wake. But with a DEA agent closing in on him, things could get complicated...
name: Chapter Three

description: The epic "Death of the Family" begins in this story, reprinted for just $1.00 from BATMAN #13, with pages from the 2016 edition of the DC ESSENTIALS CATALOGUE!

volume.name: DC Comics Essentials: Batman: Death of the Family

description: The past washes over the chimps as repressed memories continue to surface. It’s clear that Professor Heisler will stop at nothing to make this experimental program a success.
name: Chapter Three

description: Catwoman's departure from the insurgency seems complete as she returns to her life of crime. Harley decides to join her for a bit of fun. But things turn grim as they run into Damian, who is undergoing a transformation himself...into the new Nightwing!
name: Taking Sides

volume.name: Injustice: Gods Among Us Year Five

description:
The first arc of Kodoja reaches its action-packed conclusion! The battle between Kodoja and the giant serpent reaches its conclusion in Port Emerald at the base of Terror Mountain! Amidst the fury of the giant monster fight, General Cruz continues her dangerous mission in the field to stop Kodoja and end the rampage... while the mystery around the Secretary of Defense's suicide earlier in the day continues to unravel.

Note: The digital edition (4/6/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.

From the Shuster award winning creators of Least I Could Do and Gutters comes a loving nod to classic fantasy novels that manages to flip the genre on it's head. Unlikely heros cut a swath through a fantasy world that is extremely familiar and yet very different. A naive elven hunter makes an strange friend in an undead warlock and the two manage to make both enemies and friends as they fight the good fight against the Legaran Empire.

Marie is 12 years old when she finds her village has been destroyed, her parents murdered, and her brothers and sisters reduced to slavery. She swears that, one day, she will take revenge for this...

Fifteen years later, Marie has become a fighter who sells her skills to the highest bidder. With her friend and blood-brother, William, she fights the 'Dragons' – strange creatures that hover on the borderline of reality. Marie is the only person who can see them and confront them. That's when she finds herself on the trail of one of her family's murderers. Will she be able to avenge her family? And are her strange abilities linked to the slaughter that occurred when she was a child?
name: Armance

description:
Marie is a fighter who sells her skills to the highest bidder. With her friend and blood brother, William, she fights the 'Dragons' – strange creatures that hover on the borderline of reality.

Along with her sister Armance, Marie is in search of Georges d'Aiscelin, one of the murderers responsible for the massacre of their family, fifteen years earlier. Having lost his trail and needing money, they accept an apparently simple mission; to escort a monk and a treasure of the French church safely out of the kingdom of Milan...

But soon, on the road through the Alps, the pursuit becomes a deadly struggle. Furthermore, the shade of the cruel Georges d'Aiscelin, and Lou, the young brother of Marie, overshadows their path.
name: Revenge

description:
Marie is a fighter who sells her skills to the highest bidder. With her friend and blood brother, William, she fights the 'Dragons' – strange creatures that hover on the borderline of reality.

Under the gaze of Edouard III, sovereign of England, a tournament has been organized, to fight monsters made of pasteboard, and beautiful Marie will be the guest of honor... But the young woman is still looking for her brother Amaury, sold as slave when he was eight years old. And to overcome the French armies, the king of England schemes to call upon dark forces - the real monsters, made of horror and hatred, which Marie has been fighting for a long time...

Knights are competing against each other to impress noble ladies, swords are colliding, worlds are tearing apart, and atrocities are showing up... And Marie has to choose her side.
name: Amaury

description:
Marie is a fighter who sells her skills to the highest bidder. With her friend and blood brother, William, she fights the 'Dragons' – strange creatures that hover on the borderline of reality.

Without William's help, she would never have survived. Now William has disappeared, has been kidnapped. And the ransom to get him back? Keys... The keys to unlocking the mystery of this world, the answers behind its creation. In Bayeux, the Emperor of France fights against the English in what would be, in another world, the beginning of the Hundred Years' War. And the battle does not turn in his favor. But there is so much more at stake than the fate of France...
name: William

description: Marvel is happy to present the launch new stories starting NOW! and introducing the Road to Civil War II! This will be your first look into Marvel's upcoming story-lines for Spring 2016 leading into the most anticipated sequel of the ground breaking event of 2006, Civil War!

volume.name: Marvel New Stories Road To Civil War II Previews

description: The Avengers are a larger-than-life super hero team, which is why ANT-MAN feels a little bit out of place on the team. So, he's taking a little time for himself and heading out to the west coast! His vacation gets cut short, though, when a mysterious woman brings a murder mystery to his front door. Even worse, Tony Stark's father is the prime suspect!

Time traveler Ben's lifelong desire to discover the truth behind his father's disappearance has led to a path of destruction, putting his loved ones in harm's way. Now he will do anything to reverse these events even if that means putting an end to his own life before he was ever born! All paths lead to this moment in time in this shattering conclusion to the 4-part series based on events from the sci-fi movie Narcopolis.

The creatures reach Dragon Lake. But it's not what they expected.

September 21st, 2019 – 13:13 pm

After a successful take-off, the Atlantis Shuttle disappears mysteriously from control screens.

September 22nd, 2019 – 13:13 pm

All the timepieces (watches, clocks...) on the planet suddenly stop.

September 23rd, 2019 – 13:13 pm

The Atlantis Shuttle reappears and lands in Cape Canaveral, with only one survivor is on board: the commanding officer of the mission is found in a state of shock right in the middle of his crew's torn appart corpses.

September 24th, 2019 – 13:13 pm

An American nuclear submarine gets the echo sonar of a German U-boat that had disappeared sixty eight years earlier... In open sea, a trawler discovers the monumental hull of the Titanic, that sank in the same place, 650 km in the Southeast of Newfoundland.

And that's just a beginning... As the threat of Apocalypse hangs over the whole planet, it would seem that the future of Humanity has plunged into obscurity... presaging the worst for our civilisation.
name: Atlantis

description:
As the threat of Apocalypse hangs over the whole planet, it would seem that the future of Humanity has been plunged into chaos and obscurity... Heralding the worst for civilization.

What will be the next disaster? Is humanity ready to face it? And what are these mysterious "ghost ships" roaming the seas and space?
name: Project Blue Beam

description:
While the United States are accused of wanting to found a New World Order, disasters continue to go on all around the world, and the secret Apollo XX mission lands on the moon where they make a major discovery...

At the same time, in the logbook of the captain of the Titanic - returned to the surface in an almost new state - a strange address and phone number is found, which seems to indicate a location in the Bahamas where a blue hole has formed! And a team of specialists is gathered to dive into this mysterious abyss...
name: Exogenesis

description:
While the United States are accused of wanting to found a New World Order, the disasters continue around the world, causing riots, tensions to rise, and the possibility of war.

What really happened to the Titanic, which led it to navigate at full steam? And a probe has been sent into the blue hole of the Bahamas, but what is hiding on the other side of the mirror?
name: Mantique

description:
2166, THE ERA OF THE APOCALYPSE ENTERS ITS FINAL PHASE - THE LAST TIMES.

In a world dominated by religious zeal and politics, in the New Jerusalem that has become the center of the world, a destructive God has been created by a group of religious fanatics.

Yiu, a mercenary killer paid by the clergy, having completed her last mission by eliminating Shu Fat, is about to undertake her next - to hunt and eliminate the nascent God.
name: The Promise I Made To You
